field.name: AbbreviatedPrice

Contract Price
Price of the leg can be expressed as
(a) Explicit Price (e.g. 7589)
Explicit Price is a positive number without any prefix.
(b) A price code expression (e.g. S + 10 which means settlement price plus ten)
Valid price codes are S, YS, C, V ,M & B (basis)
(c) A differential (e.g. -10 which means ten units lower than the price of the first leg)
A valid differential is a number prefixed with either (+) or( - )

field.name: Quoting Duration
field.description:
Quoting Duration is a user defined integer field for users to specify the type of quoting or quote streaming desired from the price making system. Valid Values:
0 = One-shot Quoting (RFQ) (A maximum of only one Quote is allowed per Quote Request. If the price maker withdraws a quoted price, the Quote Request associated with that transaction will be terminated. Price taker decision to accept or reject the quote will also terminate the process)
>0 = Auction Period Streaming (The price maker can quote as often as it likes within a specified time period. Each new quote intended to replace the previous. In this case, price maker withdrawals of a previous quoted price will not terminate the Quote Request process. Only an explicit request to abort the Quote Request by the price maker will terminate the process. Price taker decision to accept or reject the quote will also terminate the process.)
. -1 = Stream Till Done (Similar to Auction Period Streaming model with the exception that there is no pre-defined auction period. Price taker decision to accept or reject the quote will also terminate the process)
-2 = Stream Till Cancelled (Similar to the Stream Till Done model with the exception that when the price taker accepts a given quote it does not result in the termination of the quoting process. Quoting continues indefinitely until one of the parties explicitly cancels the Quote Request transaction).

field.name: AffirmationIndicator
field.description: Indicates the role of the party affirming the trade. Valid Values: 0 = Trade not yet affirmed (in confirmation stage), 1 = trade affirmed by Agent, 2 = trade affirmed by Institution, 3 = affirming party not specified (trade affirmed by Agent as determined by DTCC), 4 = affirming party not specified (trade affirmed by Institution as determined by DTCC), 5 = trade affirmed by customer or interested party

field.name: ShortSaleRestriction
field.description:
Same as tag 1687 (int datatype). To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions.
Indicates whether a restriction applies to short selling a security.
Valid values: 0 = No restrictions 1 = Security is not shortable 2 = Security not shortable at or below the best bid

field.name: ShortSaleExemptionReason
field.description:
Same as tag 1688 (int datatype). To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. Indicates the reason a short sale order is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.).
Valid values: 0 = Exemption Reason Unknown 1 = Incoming Short Sale Exempt 2 = Above National Best Bid (Broker Dealer Provision) 3 = Delayed Delivery 4 = Odd-Lot 5 = Domestic Arbitrage 6 = International Arbitrage 7 = Underwriter or Syndicate Distribution 8 = Riskless Principal 9 = VWAP

field.name: LegShortSaleExemptionReason
field.description:
Same as tag 1689 (int datatype). To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. Use in LegOrdGrp, InstrmtLegExecGrp, TrdInstrmtLegGrp components.
Indicates the reason a short sale is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.)
Uses same values as ShortSaleExemptionReason.

field.name: SideShortSaleExemptionReason
field.description:
Same as tag 1690 (int datatype). To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. Indicates the reason a short sale is exempted from applicable regulation (e.g. Reg SHO addendum (b)(1) in the U.S.)
Uses same values as ShortSaleExemptionReason.

field.name: CustodialLotID
field.description:
String datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. An opaque identifier used to communicate the custodians identifier for the lot. It is expected that this information would be provided by the custodian as part of a reconciliation process that occurs before trading.
Used in AllocAckGrp, AllocGrp, PreAllocGrp, PreAllocMlegGrp, TrdAllocGrp

field.name: CurrentCostBasis
field.description:
Amt datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. The amount that the current shares are worth. If this lot was liquidated, the total gain/loss for a trade is equal to the trade amount minus the current cost basis.
Used in AllocAckGrp, AllocGrp, PreAllocGrp, PreAllocMlegGrp, TrdAllocGrp

field.name: LegCustodialLotID
field.description: String datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. An opaque identifier used to communicate the custodians identifier for the lot. It is expected that this information would be provided by the custodian as part of a reconciliation process that occurs before trading.

field.name: LegVSPDate
field.description: LocalMktDate datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. The Versus Purchase Date used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.

field.name: LegVSPPrice
field.description: Price datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. The Versus Purchase Price used to identify the lot in situations where a custodial lot identifier is not available.The value should be calculated based on current cost basis / quantity held.

field.name: LegCurrentCostBasis
field.description: Amt datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. The amount that the current shares are worth. If this lot was liquidated, the total gain/loss for a trade is equal to the trade amount minus the current cost basis.

field.name: LastLiquidityInd
field.description: Same as LastLiqudityInd, tag 851, in FIX 4.4 and above. To be used by implementations that cannot support tag 851 in FIX 4.3 and below.

field.name: EventTimeUnit
field.description:
String datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. Time unit associated with the event. If present EventTimePeriod must also appear and EventDate and EventTime may be omitted.
Valid Values: H Hour Min Minute S Second D Day Wk Week Mo Month Yr - Year
Added to the repeating group after EventTime.

field.name: EventTimePeriod
field.description:
Int datatype. To be used by implementations that cannot accommodate later tag numbers in earlier FIX versions. Time unit multiplier for the event. If present EventTimeUnit must also appear and EventDate and EventTime may be omitted.
Added to the repeating group after EventTimeUnit.

field.name: EQIQuoteResponseLevel
field.description: Indicates the level of acknowledgement expected for each quote that is submitted to NYSE as a Quote Advisory. Possible values:(0), or if the tag is not in the message, NYSE will not send any acknowledgement whatsoever for this message. (1), NYSE will send an acknowledgements only if this message fails one of NYSE validations.(2), NYSE will acknowledge this message in any case (rejection or acceptance).

field.name: EQIAdvisoryType
field.description: Indicates what kind of information is embedded in a quote advisory message.(0)Updated fully accepted quote.(1)Updated partially accepted quote.(2)Accepted quote but not updated.(3)Partially accepted quote but not updated.(4)Rejected quote

field.name: EQIQuoteOrigin
field.description: Indicates origin of the quote:whether the quote was generated by NYSE Display Book or by a quote submitted from the firm.(E)The quote was generated because of a quote submitted by the firm.(D)The quote was generated by NYSE DBK(e.g. manual quote entered by specialist).

field.name: NYSEQuoteRefId
field.description: Provides support for cross-referencing the quote in a Quote Advisory message to a quote submitted to NYSE. field.name: OppSidePeg
field.description: Tag had previously been named XpressIndicator, datatype remains Char. 4th Qtr, 2011. Opposite Side Pegging. This indicator specifies whether the customer has specified Pegging functionality be applied to the Opposite Side PBBO for the d-Quote or s-Quote. Value = "Y" or "N". Not Boolean so invalid value will be rejected by CCG/ME, not Fix Parser. Tag 9561, PegInd, used for same side Pegging and 'Y' value mutually exclusive with 'Y' value for OppSidePeg.

field.name: OffsetPrice
field.description: Price Format- tag had previously been named XpressTime datatype format UTCTimeOnly. 4th Qtr, 2011. Retail Price Improvement Orders or CCG s-Quotes shall have a price improvement offset value in this tag which may have a value of zero to be filed better than the PBBO subject to limit price and cap rules. This tag may also be used in Pegging d-quotes and s-quotes on same side or opposite side pegging to the PBBO, i.e. peg to PBO for buy pegging; PBB for sell pegging, offset by the price increments based on this tag's absolute Offset value.

field.name: WriteInTime
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture Field (FESC): This is an optional field that may be used in the case of a system failure or otherwise, to indicate the actual time an order was received on the Floor, if prior to the time that the order is actually recorded in the system. This field allows members to synchronize their electronic order records with time-stamped paper tickets when used in situations such as system failures. Note that an As Of indicator flag must always be set when order details are being recorded late due to a system failure, regardless of whether a Write In time is entered.

field.name: AsOfIndicator
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: A flag that is manually entered by a user to indicate that an order or order modification was represented at a point of sale on the NYSE trading floor before being entered into a system. Such orders and order modifications are referred to as "late entered orders." The AsOfIndicator should only be used in situations where orders are entered into a system late due to system failure. The AsOfIndicator must be transmitted to the NYSE with all late entered orders and order modifications and Drop Copies of such. Value, when tag is present = A.

field.name: DropCopyFlag
field.description: NYSE - A flag that indicates that a message is a Drop Copy. This flag is required in all Drop Copy messages sent to FESC or from CMS. Valid Values: C = CMS, D = FESC, 1 = Order Drop Copy, 2 = Execution Report Drop Copy, 3 = Admin Inquiry Drop Copy, 4 = Admin Response Drop Copy, 5 = Clearance Drop Copy. An alpha value must appear in combination with a numeric value, separated by a space.

field.name: SolicitedFlag
field.description:
FCS Order, Cancel, Cancel/Repl, Report. Indicates whether or not the order was solicited. Valid Values: Y = Was Solicited N = Was Not Solicited SolicitedFlag [9442] is for use in FIX 4.1 only and corresponds to tag SolicitedFlag [377] in FIX 4.2.
FIX.4.1 Format: Char FIX.4.2 Format: Boolean

field.name: RepStatReq
field.description:
FCS Admin Request - Line 2, Field 1
Valid Values: 1 = Check^Price 2 = Confirm^Contra 3 = Confirm^Qty^Executed Contains Admin message type and must include the original order instruction. Tags OrdStatReq [9424] and RepStatReq [9443] are mutually exclusive, either [9424] or [9425] must appear in Message Type H. FIX.4.1 Format: Char, FIX.4.2 Format: String.

field.name: SponsoringFirm
field.description: Member firm sponsoring the institution submitting orders.

field.name: LvsTimeInForce
field.description: FCS Cancel - Line 3E, Field 2 Valid Values: 0 = DAY, 1 = GTC, 2 = OPG, 3 = OC, 4 = FOK, 5 = GTX, 6 = Reject Message, set Text[58] to |Good till date not supported|. Allows the user to change the Time In Force on a Cancel with Leaves. Absence of this field defaults to original order state. Note: Original Time In Force can be re-stated. FIX 4.1 Format: Char, FIX 4.2 Format: String

field.name: CMSType
field.description: Provides further classification of the Execution Report FIX Message Type 8 for CMS' use. Valid values: A = Admin Response, P = SPARS, R = Execution Report, S = Status Message (Status Messages include Rejects, Restarts and Drop Copy). Format FIX 4.1 Char, FIX 4.2 String.

field.name: CAPIndicator
field.description: NYSE - Indicates a conversion and parity order (CAP). Required on all CAP Orders, CAP Cancels and CAP Cancel Replace Requests. Valid Value = Y. Format = Char

field.name: BrokerBadge#
field.description: Represents the initiating Broker Badge Number. Required on all CAP Orders. Value is up to 4 numeric characters. Format = Char

field.name: BillTo
field.description: Represents the Badge or Commission Billing Number. Required on all CAP Orders. Value = up to 4 alpha/numeric characters. Must be either ALL numeric or ALL alpha. Format = Char

field.name: ParentOrdXRefId
field.description: Represents the Member Firm of the Parent Order plus the Parent Order Id currently sent to FESC. Required on all CAP Orders. Value must be a valid NYSE Member Firm Mnemonic Identifier followed by one space, followed by the Parent Order Id that is currently sent to FESC. Value = 4 character alpha for Member Firm of the Parent Order, one space, up to 22 characters using ASCII character set from Octal 40 (Hex 20) to Octal 176 (Hex 7E) for the Parent Order Id. Format = string.

field.name: ParentFirmOrdId
field.description: Tag 9451 = Parent Order ID required for NYSE BBSS entered CAP orders. 1 to 4 alpha characters Branch Code, followed by a space followed by 1 to 5 characters numeric Branch Sequence followed by a slash character ("/") followed by the CMS Session date. Format = string

field.name: NYSETANum
field.description: The turn around number of the Parent Order, required only for NYSE BBSS entered CAP orders. 6 characters - 2 alpha characters followed by 4 numeric characters OR 3 alpha characters followed by 3 numeric characters. Format = string

field.name: ParentFirm
field.description: Valid NYSE Member Firm Mnemonic. Must be present on all NYSE BBSS CAP orders. 1 to 4 alpha characters. Format = string.

field.name: ContraClrFirm
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture Field (FESC): This is a required field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies the clearing firm mnemonic (as assigned by the NYSE) of the contra side of a trade.

field.name: EnteringFirm
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: This is a required field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies the mnemonic (as assigned by the NYSE) of the member or member organization which recorded the order details (as required by Rule 123e).

field.name: OrderRefDate
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: This is a required field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies the date the order was entered into an Exchange system.

field.name: OCSControlNum
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: This is an optional field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies the NYSE Online Comparison System (OCS) control number that is returned to the firm by OCS after submission of a side.

field.name: MajorBadge
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: This is a required field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies the badge number of the executing broker of its (the submitters) side of the trade

field.name: SpecialTradeInd
field.description: NYSE - Front End Systemic Capture (FESC) Field: This is an optional field when submitting a report drop copy. Specifies any special trade indication: ' ' = Not a special trade 'X' = Special trade 'E' = Ex-clearing trade

field.name: OrderCapacity2
field.description: NYSE - Additional value representing Account Type. Account Type Q indicates a trade to cover an error transaction. Format = char. Valid Value = Q

field.name: AddQty
field.description: NYSE - Represents the additional (increased amount) order quantity requested. Required on all Makes orders (Message Type G format). Format in 4.1 = int, Format in 4.2 = Qty.

field.name: PrinIndicator
field.description: The indicator that denotes the specialist was involved in the trade. contains value 00 or 01.

field.name: SubscriptionRequestType
field.description: Addition of a SubscriptionRequestType for Security Definition Request to enable FIX 4.3 like functionality for FIX 4.2 users

field.name: PrinCommentCode
field.description: 2-byte alpha code that the specialist inserts into the execution report

field.name: OrderOrigin
field.description: For submission of order originator (String)to specify Exchange:Firm Acronym. Of the form [Exchange:]Acronym If [Exchange:] is omitted, the Target Exchange is assumed. E.g. CBOE:ABC and ABC are equivalent for firm Acronym ABC at Exchange CBOE for orders sent to Exchange CBOE.

field.name: RejectReasonCode
field.description: Reject reason code indicating the reason why the message was rejected.

field.name: EquitySession
field.description: This field will (optionally) be used to specify the Equity Session when defining "Buy Write" or "Covered Call" type strategies.

field.name: UserAssignedCancelID
field.description: User assigned cancel id for an order. Work around - future version will revert to standard FIX order cancel request handling

field.name: ExtendedPriceType
field.description: For using PriceTypes in addition to the current FIX 4.2 Tag 40 validations (e.g. like the FIX 4.4 Tag 423 values)

field.name: QuoteOrigin
field.description: This parameter is used to indicate the origin of the quote entry. It must take one of the following values: 6 - Public Customer 7 - Broker 8 - Market Maker

field.name: NoTransactionCosts
field.description: Repeating group under the trade capture suite of messages

field.name: TransactionCostTypes
field.description: Repeating group under the transaction cost for Trade Capture reporting

field.name: TransactionCostCode
field.description: Repeating group under transaction costs

field.name: TransactionCostRate
field.description: Repeating group under transaction cost group

field.name: TransactionCostFlag
field.description: Repeating group under transaction costs.

field.name: TransactionCostAmt
field.description: Repeating group under the transaction costs group

field.name: TransactionCostCurrency
field.description: Repeating field under the transaction costs group

field.name: e-QuoteType
field.description: Represents an e-Quote Type.

field.name: DisplayIndicator
field.description: Specifies if the Broker interest is part of the NYSE BBO and is visible to the specialist.

field.name: ReservePublishQty
field.description: Required for Reserve e-Quote types. Represents the publish quantity.

field.name: eQuoteId
field.description: Unique identifier of the eQuote must be unique within broker badge associates the eQuote with its underlying orders

field.name: LayerLinkId
field.description: Unique identifier must be unique within broker badge associates the layers of a layered eQuote

field.name: DBKLinkId
field.description: Ensures reports to underlying orders are linked back to the e-Quote execution report.

field.name: NumULID
field.description: Number of repeats in the repeating group

field.name: ULProprietaryCode
field.description: Indicates whether the underlying order ID is the ID of a proprietary OMS

field.name: ULDisposeCode
field.description: Indicates the disposition of the order ID; supports the ability to add or remove orders that underlie the eQuote.

field.name: RoutingInstruction
field.description: Routing instruction

field.name: ERCActivityType
field.description: 1 alpha-numeric code that designates the type of activity against the order; i.e., original execution, correction, bust, etc.

field.name: OmgeoNoSWIFTDifferences
field.description: null

field.name: OmgeoNoTLL2FieldsSameValueEval
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Number of repeating groups of (maximum of 40) trade level L2 fields and the field's same value evaluation

field.name: OmgeoTLL2FieldName
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Name of L2 Field.

field.name: OmgeoTLL2SameValue
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Indicates if the value of the OmgeoTLL2FieldName supplied by the Broker is the same as the value supplied by the Investment Manager.

field.name: OmgeoNoTDL2FieldsSameValueEval
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Number of repeating groups of (maximum of 40) trade detail L2 fields and the field's same value evaluation.

field.name: OmgeoTDL2FieldName
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Name of L2 Field.

field.name: OmgeoTDL2SameValue
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Indicates if the value of the OmgeoTDL2FieldName supplied by the Broker is the same as the value supplied by the Investment Manager.

field.name: OmgeoTDSAFENCSD
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Indicates the SWIFT BIC of the national central security depository, where the security will be safekept.

field.name: OmgeoTDSAFEICSD
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Indicates the SWIFT BIC of an international central securities depository, where the security will be safekept.

field.name: OmgeoTDSAFECUST
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Indicates the SWIFT BIC of a global custodian bank, where the security will be safekept.

field.name: OmgeoTDSAFESHHE
field.description: Omgeo CTM specific field. Text that indicates that the shares to be safekept will be held elsewhere.

field.name: SubRule80A
field.description: Additional flag to Rule80A (aka Order Capacity/Account Type)

field.name: BidPriceType
field.description: Determines the type of price contained in the quote message. A=actual (default); S=spread to benchmark; D=discount to yield; Y=yield to maturity; P=convertible spread to parity; V=convertible vs stock; OW=Offer wanted; U=unpriced

field.name: OfferPriceType
field.description: Determines the type of price contained in the quote message. A=actual (default), S=spread to benchmark, D=discount to yield, Y=yield to maturity, P=convertible spread to parity, V=convertible vs. stock, BW=Bid wanted, BW U=unpriced

field.name: FlatFlag
field.description: Identifies a quote for a security which is traded flat N=No; Y=Yes

field.name: HedgeRatio
field.description: Hedge ratio e.g. 70.00 indicating 70% of associated stock in relation to quoted stock

field.name: MarketMakerName
field.description: Name of market maker

field.name: LockCrossFlag
field.description: If set to Y, forces a price (quote or advertisement) to be accepted even if the price is out of range. N=No, default Y=Yes, force price to be accepted even if out of range.

field.name: NegativeBidPxFlag
field.description: If present and set to Y, indicates that the price held in the price field (BidPx) should be treated as a negative value. N=No, the BidPx price is a positive value Y=Yes, the BidPx price is a negative value

field.name: NegativeOfferPxFlag
field.description: If present and set to Y, indicates that the price held in the price field (OfferPx) should be treated as a negative value. N=No, the OfferPx price is a positive value Y=Yes, the OfferPx price is a negative value

field.name: NQBSecurityID
field.description: A unique ID for security, issued by NQB

field.name: PurgeStatusFlag
field.description: N=purge starting, vendor should purge the database; Y=purge complete

field.name: PurgeSequenceNumber
field.description: A unique sequence number present in application messages during a purge, enabling Vendors to track progress of the purge.

field.name: PurgeMessageCount
field.description: Total number of messages that were sent during a purge

field.name: PurgeReason
field.description: Indicates the reason for a database purge: 1=refresh at start of day; 2=as requested

field.name: OTCBBFlag
field.description: Indicates whether a Quote in the EQS is from the OTCBB N=Not from the OTCBB Y=From the OTCBB

field.name: Service
field.description: Indicates the NQB service under which a security is quoted. OP=Pink Sheets OY=Yellow Sheets OPL=Partnership Sheets OG=Global Quote

field.name: NoCompetingQuotes
field.description: eg. MSFT, 'Bloomberg Indicative'

field.name: CompetingQuoteDealer
field.description: eg. MSFT, 'Bloomberg Indicative'

field.name: CompetingQuote
field.description: Actual quote for a security or for first leg of a swaps trade

field.name: Coupon
field.description: Coupon rate of bond

field.name: CompetingQuoteLeg2
field.description: Actual quote of second leg (Swaps only)

field.name: CompetingQuoteFwdPoints
field.description: Fwd/Swap points (Swaps/Outrights only)

field.name: PiggybackFlag
field.description: Indicates if a security is qualified as 15c12-11 "Piggyback" exempt: Y=Yes; N=No

field.name: CompetingQuoteType
field.description: 1 - Indicative 2 - Executable

field.name: TradingSuspendFlag
field.description: Indicates if trading in the security has been halted for any reason: Y=Yes; N=No

field.name: NoReRoutedOrders
field.description: Defines the number of Orders rerouted to another broker.

field.name: Re-RoutedOrderId
field.description: Denotes the Order # of a Re-Routed Order.

field.name: ShortName
field.description: Short name of security

field.name: BenchIDSource
field.description: Identifies the class of associated alternative BenchSecurityID used to define the underlying benchmark for Spread to Benchmark quotes

field.name: BrokerFirmID
field.description: Identifies the firm associated with the IntroducingBadgeID[9448]

field.name: BenchSecurityID
field.description: The security ID used to define the benchmark security in the Spread to Benchmark quote, further qualified by the BenchIDSource field which determines the identification system

field.name: UndSymbol
field.description: Contains the security symbol for the underlying security of convertible securities for convertible spread to parity and convertible vs. stock quotes. The symbol is further qualified by the UndSymbolSfx and UndSecurityExchange fields.

field.name: UndSymbolSfx
field.description: Additional information about the underlying security (e.g. preferred, wts, etc.) underlying the quote, with an absence of the field indicating common for equities.

field.name: UndStockPrice
field.description: The stock price of the underlying security for convertible spread to parity and convertible vs. stock quotes.

field.name: UnsolicitedFlag
field.description: Indicates if the quote is to be treated as solicited or unsolicited: Y=Unsolicited agency order, N=Principal or Solicited Agency

field.name: OmgeoSwiftFieldName
field.description: null

field.name: TraderID
field.description: Identifies a trader

field.name: MMLocation
field.description: Text describing a market maker location (i.e. geopraphic location and/or desk)

field.name: MarketMakerID
field.description: The market maker ID to be shown against a quote

field.name: ItemID
field.description: A sequence identifier permitting a series of updates to be ordered in time

field.name: UpdateType
field.description: Indicates the nature of a 'database update' message: 1=Update; 2=New; 3=Delete

field.name: StateOrCountry
field.description: For a US address specifies the state. For non-US address specifies the country

field.name: Telephone1
field.description: A phone number

field.name: USFirmFlag
field.description: Indicates if the firm is resident in the US for the purpose of quotes generated by its traders. Y=Yes, a US based firm, N=N, a non US firm

field.name: UndSecurityExchange
field.description: Qualifies the UndSymbolID (UndSymbolID, UndSymbolSfx) supplied to define the symbol as issued by what exchange.

field.name: Telephone2
field.description: A phone number

field.name: MaturityDate
field.description: The securities maturity date expressed as a single field rather than using the existing FIX fields of MaturityMonthYear and MaturityDay

field.name: NQBIssuerID
field.description: Used to track securities from the same issuer

field.name: OpenFlag
field.description: Indicates if Trader at Market Maker is open for trading or closed. Only quotes of open Traders should be considered live.

field.name: InternalRef
field.description: Internal reference assigned to an order into the GL server.

field.name: SecondaryAccount
field.description: Assigned by a party which originates the order to the exchange.

field.name: DSS
field.description: Differed Settlement Service. Valid Values : 0=No 1=Yes

field.name: GLID
field.description: GL key used to identify the exchange and the market into GL servers.

field.name: Split
field.description: Identicates the type of order splitting.

field.name: DataBaseIndex
field.description: Index of record into the GL server database.

field.name: AccountType
field.description: Type of account: 'S' Speculator, 'M' Market Maker, 'H' Hedge

field.name: MITFlag
field.description: Market If Touch flag: Valid values: '0' Simple Order (default), '1' MIT order type.

field.name: ActOnImbalance
field.description: Boolean: Determines whether the strategy reacts to published closing auction imbalances. Default = True

field.name: PrinChangeIndicator
field.description: 1 byte numeric that denotes that a previously-reported Prin execution has been changed to non-Prin

field.name: OmgeoSwiftTagQualifier
field.description: null

field.name: EquoteExecType
field.description: This field indicates that the e-Quote report was executed with Discretion, Pegging or Both. The following values represent: "1" - Executed with Discretion "2" - Executed with Pegging "3" - Executed with Discretion and Pegging

field.name: PegInd
field.description: This indicator specifies whether the customer has specified Pegging functionality for the e-Quote or d-Quote. Value = "Y"

field.name: CeilingFloorPrice
field.description: This field specifies the highest (for a buy) or lowest (for a sell) price to which the e-Quote or d-Quote may peg. Price including decimal (must be multiple of MPV and valid Price Unit).

field.name: MinPegQty
field.description: This field indicates the smallest size quote to which the e-Quote or d-Quote is willing to peg. Must be roundlot represented in shares.

field.name: MaxPegQty
field.description: These fields indicate the largest size quote to which the e-Quote or d-Quote is willing to peg. Must be roundlot represented in shares.

field.name: DiscPriceRange
field.description: The range within which a d-Quote can reach to trade with discretion, as initiating interest. The range is specified as the number of cents (or MPVs) of price discretion above (for a Buy) or below (for a Sell) the discretionary e-Quotes currently filed price. Price including decimal (must be multiple of MPV and valid Price Unit)

field.name: DiscMaxVol
field.description: This field specifies the quantity the e-Quote is willing to use to trade with pricing discretion. When an e-Quote has a quantity designated to trade with pricing discretion, that quantity is referred to as a d-Quote. Must be Roundlot represented in shares.

field.name: ITSAllInd
field.description: This indicator identifies whether the customer has specified that the e-Quote may be shipped to better ITS quotes within its Discretionary Range, even when not required to facilitate a trade at the NYSE. Value = "Y" or "N"

field.name: OppSideMinSize
field.description: This field specifies the smallest size the d-Quote is willing to initiate a trade against with discretion. This size may be applied to an incoming order or to aggregate interest at a price point, as specified in later requirements. Must be Roundlot represented in shares.

field.name: OppSideMaxSize
field.description: This field specifies the largest size the d-Quote is willing to initiate a trade against with discretion. This size may be applied to an incoming order or to aggregate interest at a price point, as specified in later requirements. Must be Roundlot represented in shares.

field.name: ExecAwayMktInd
field.description: Executed Away Market Indicator containing a value representing the exchange away from the NYSE where the order was executed. To be used in Fix MsgType 8 as an optional tag for reports and corrections, the values not being Fix Standard. Values are SIAC internal values, A = Amex;B = Boston;C = NSE;D = NASD;I = ISE;M = CSE;P = Pacific/Archipelago;T = NASDAQ;W = CBOE;X = Philadelphia;

field.name: NoTapePrintFlag
field.description: A flag, when true (Y), indicating that this trade was not printed to tape. Default is 'N' if tag not present. Used in Exec Report, Fix Msg Type 8.

field.name: TotalOddLotBuyAlarm
field.description: null

field.name: OddLotImbalanceShares
field.description: null

field.name: StagingTargetPrice
field.description: Target Price at which an order will stage and monitor

field.name: StageOrderIsInquiry
field.description: Denotes whether a staged order is an inquiry order.

field.name: TargetPriceType
field.description: Target price type valid values: 1 - Price 2 - Yield 3 - Spread

field.name: ExecutionType
field.description: Execution type that, among other values, contains a value for odd-lot adjustments to be used by SPAR users

field.name: BillingIndicator
field.description: Execution Report Billing categories (valid on regular executions, AWOs, and ERCs) Valid values: 1=Taker; 2=Provider; 3=Blended; 4=Opening/Provider; 5=Opening/Blended; 6=Closing/Provider; 7=CLosing/Blended; 8=Specialist; Data Type: Char

field.name: ExpERCReferenceNumber
field.description: FIX 4.2 Format: String 10-byte Expanded Activity ID associated with an Execution Report. This tag is a concatenation of a 5-digit Reference number, followed by a 5-digit Sequence number. Both reference number and sequence number will start at 00001 (i.e. 0000100001). For each new activity, the Reference and Sequence number will increment by one. The Reference number will remain the same when a modification was performed on a specific activity.

field.name: ParentID
field.description: Contains the OrderID of the parent order for a child order.

field.name: OrderId
field.description: Contains the GL SLE ID of the order.

field.name: ChildID
field.description: Contains the GL SLE ID of the child order.

field.name: MIFID Internalization Indicator
MIFID Best Execution Indicator
MIFID Split
field.description: Autorizes the split functionality. Valid values: 1=YES; 2=NO. Default value=2(NO).

field.name: MIFID Retention
field.description: Equivalent of Overnight. It's for keeping the orders until the next trading session. Valid values: 1=YES; 2=NO. Default value=2(NO).

field.name: MIFID Destination
Trade Type Indicator
MIFID Negociation code
field.description: This field contains the negociation code of execution market

field.name: Update Reason
field.description: This field is used to filter specific GL messages into GL FIX IN

field.name: Price Checking Flag
field.description: Used to reject the order if the price is too far away from the market. Valid values: 0=No price control (default value); 1=Price control; 2=Severe; 3=Client not sure.

field.name: Quantity control
field.description: Indicates whether the market exchange has to check the quantity order. Valid values: 0=No check (default value); 1=Check quantity (big size).

field.name: StartTime
field.description: UTC Timestamp. Time/date combination represented in UTC in either YYYYMMDD-HH:MM:SS (whole seconds) or YYYYMMDD-HH:MM:SS.sss (milliseconds) format. Colons,dash, and period required.

field.name: EndTime
field.description: UTC Timestamp. Time/date combination represented in UTC in either YYYYMMDD-HH:MM:SS (whole seconds) or YYYYMMDD-HH:MM:SS.sss (milliseconds) format. Colons,dash, and period required.

field.name: GL Routing Reference
field.description: Free format text string for internal client use. Max size is 255 char.

field.name: Client Free Field 1
field.description: Free format text string for internal client use. Max size is 16 char.

field.name: Client Free Field 2
field.description: Free format text string for internal client use. Max size is 32 char.

field.name: CV Instruction
field.description: Specifies ClearVision (GL Back Office) Instruction. Valid values: 0=Default value; 1=Send To ClearVision; 2=Save in GL OMS.

field.name: ETBegin
field.description: Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field and others between 9599 and 9699 (TRIAD Financial Server)

field.name: Password
field.description:
Password field used for secondary validation/security authorization.
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: IoiNatural
field.description:
Additional Natural criteria field.
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: IoiType
field.description:
Additional IoiType field used for discrimination on systems that express additional flavors of Iois
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: NoFixStatusses
field.description:
Specifies number of FIX Status messages to follow : repeating group
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: FIXStatus
field.description:
Specifies status of FIX Connection: 0 or 1, = Up or Down
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: FIXStatusSubID
field.description:
Specifies status of FIX SubID Connection: 0 or 1, = Up or Down
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: FIXStatusOBOCompID
field.description:
Specifies status of FIX OBO CompID Connection: 0 or 1, = Up or Down
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: FIXStatusOBOSubID
field.description:
Specifies status of FIX OBO SubID Connection: 0 or 1, = Up or Down
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: FIXReferenceNumber
field.description:
Specifies refernce number of FIX forwarded message, used in returned status messages UU/UV/UW
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: ETLast
field.description:
Specifies end of custom communications.
(TRIAD Financial Server) Please contact John Douglas of Ease Technologies for information concerning this field.

field.name: NoNotes
field.description: Number of repeating notes fields

field.name: NoteType
field.description: Repeating field in the notes group

field.name: NoteId
field.description: Repeating field in the notes group

field.name: NoteText
field.description: Repeating field in the notes group

field.name: ATSAccess
field.description: ATS Access

field.name: WorkedVolumeTarget
field.description: Percentage: Volume target for the worked portion of the order.

field.name: ATSAccessType
field.description: ATS Access Type P = Passive W = I Would (cross)

field.name: ModifySequence
field.description: Count of accepted cancel/replaces.

field.name: CondPctQty
field.description: Percent of inbound OrdQty that this conditional order will interact with

field.name: CancelOrigOnReject
field.description:
Y = cancel original order if OrigClOrdId is live but modification must be rejected. (An "unsolicited" cancel will be sent for OrigClOrdId in addition to the replacement reject).
N = leave original order if modification is rejected

field.name: CorrectedPrice
field.description: On the custom UCC trade correction message, this holds the corrected price.

field.name: ECNAccessFee
field.description: Only present on fills. The total fees for this fill. Negative for rebate.

field.name: DiscretionAmount
field.description:
Amount of discretion to apply to Price.
Similar in meaning to the standard DiscretionOffset but this field is always non-negative and is implicitly added to bid prices and subtracted from offser prices.

field.name: TighterToTargetSchedule
field.description:
Int: Determines whether the strategy sticks more closely to trading schedule.
Valid Values: 0 = No (default) 100 = Yes

field.name: StrategyUrgency
field.description: Char: Used in determining the optimal trading horizon. A higher urgency corresponds with a shorter duration.

field.name: ExcludeAuctions
field.description:
Multiple Value String: Indicates which auctions should be excluded while working the order. The default is to give the strategy the discretion to participate in all auctions that are available. This field supports multiple exclusions by separating values with a space (e.g. a value of '1 4' would exclude the morning and evening auctions).
Valid Values: 1 = Morning/Opening 2 = Lunch/AM Close (Asia only) 3 = Afternoon/PM Open (Asia only) 4 = Evening/Closing

field.name: TriggerPx
field.description: Price: Identifies trigger price in absolute terms.

field.name: TriggerPxAnchor
field.description: Char: Identifies anchor price when trigger price is specified in relative terms.

field.name: AllocReceiverRole
field.description: 1 = Sender, 2 = Receiver

field.name: TriggerPxOffset

field.name: ReduceDeltaOption
field.description: Timing of delta reduction

field.name: ConditionalVolumeTarget
field.description: Percentage: Specifies target participation rate when stock price is better than user-specified trigger price.

field.name: BaseStrategy
field.description: Char: Specifies base working strategy.

field.name: ReferenceSecurityID
field.description: String: Identifies reference security.

field.name: ReferenceSecurityIDSource
field.description: String: Identifies the ID source of the reference security (tag 9633). Tag 9634 functions in the same manner as the standard FIX tag 22.

field.name: ReferenceSpread
field.description: Float: Specifies spread threshold in "BPS return since open".

field.name: MinDiscretionTime
field.description: Int: Identifies the minimum time between sweeps in seconds.

field.name: DiscretionSize
field.description: Qty: Identifies discretion threshold size in shares.

field.name: DiscretionSizePct
field.description: Percentage: Identifies discretion threshold size as a percentage of typical depth.

field.name: DiscretionRange
field.description: Float: Identifies discretion threshold range in cents.

field.name: DiscretionRangePct
field.description: Percentage: Identifies discretion threshold range as a percentage of typical spread.

field.name: ExecutionStyle
field.description:
Char: Identifies execution style in the market.
Valid Values: 1 = Quiet 2 = Neutral 3 = Aggressive

field.name: PegSpreadPct
field.description: Percentage spread for pegging

field.name: BlockFilter
field.description: Int: Specifies whether the strategy should ignore block prints.

field.name: BlockFilterManual
field.description: Qty: Allows user to specify block filter threshold in terms of a share quantity.

field.name: LimitPxType
field.description: Int: Allows users to specify an average limit price. Valid Values: 1 = Absolute Price (default) 2 = Average Limit Price

field.name: LimitPxAnchor
field.description: Char: Identifies anchor price when limit price is specified in relative terms.

field.name: LimitPxOffset
field.description: Float: Offset relative to selected anchor for relative limit price.

field.name: LimitPxDirection
field.description: Char: Identifies units and direction of relative limit price offset.

field.name: IsBuyBack
field.description: Boolean: When IsBuyBack = True, Rule 10b-18 is enabled for the trade.

field.name: DealerResponseTime
field.description: The time when Quote request will expire

field.name: SubjectTime
field.description: The time when the Quote request will become subject.

field.name: QuoteMOPLevel
field.description: Bloomberg MOP Level

field.name: SubjectOrNot
field.description: Denotes if the response is subject or not.

field.name: BLPTicketType
field.description: 1-Customer, 2-Sales

field.description: BLP Specific

field.name: Blot/Transaction Number
field.description: BLP Specific

field.name: WireTime

field.name: IsShortCover
field.description: Boolean: Decclare if the order is a short cover order (or not).

field.name: NetOrGrossIndicator
field.description: Whether price is net(0, default) or gross(1)

field.name: XbCrestRef
field.description: The Executing Broker's Crest reference

field.name: AcpCrestRef
field.description: The Accepting Counterparty's Crest reference

field.name: XbLegalDisclaimer
field.description: Executing Broker's legal disclaimer

field.name: AcpLegalDisclaimer
field.description: Accepting Counterparty's legal disclaimer

field.name: ContactPhoneNumber
field.description: Contact phone number

field.name: ContactEmailAddress
field.description: Contact email address

field.name: UnderlyingPxOffset
field.description: null

field.name: UnderlyingPxOffsetType
field.description: null

field.name: HedgeSide
field.description: Indicate Side of the hedge

field.name: OrderNote
field.description: This field is used to hold a list-level note on a list message.

field.name: OMS Version
field.description: Buy side vendor to provide the OMS software version that the trader is using to send in orders. For example: "EzeTraderConsole 4.7"

field.name: Product Version
field.description: Intended broker algo/product version with respect to the broker FIX specification version. For example: "Algo 1.0"

field.name: MinHedgeTriggerQty
field.description: Minimum option volume traded before starting the hedge

field.name: MinHedgeTriggerValue
field.description: Minimum option delta traded before starting the hedge

field.name: AutoHedge
field.description: Boolean value to indicate if option order should be hedged

field.name: AutoHedgeStrategy
field.description: Strategy used for hedging

field.name: BypassHiddenPeg
field.description: Y = Bypass hidden peg orders resting on book N (Default) = Access hidden peg orders resting on book

field.name: OrigCompID
field.description: on drop copies OrigCompID will be the TargetCompID of the original exec report (TargetCompID will be the receiver of the drop copy)

field.name: OrigSubID
field.description: on drop copies OrigSubID will be the TargetSubID of the original exec report (TargetSubID will be the receiver of the drop copy)

field.name: WorkingPrice
field.description:
If order Price had to be permanently adjusted on entry (i.e. to avoid crossing national market) the adjusted price will be reported here on the accept.
The Price field will always be a copy of the price submitted on the order.

field.name: InitialDisplayPrice
field.description: Send on Accepted and Replaced (150=0,5) execution reports when it is known that the order is being booked. Reports the price at which the order is initially displayed.

field.name: AllocRecieverRole
field.description: 1 = sender, 2 = receiver

field.name: DealerQuotePriceType
field.description: Type of DealerQuotedPrice. Same values as PriceType. Supported values: 1 = percentage (of par) 6 = spread 9 = yield

field.name: DealerQuotePrice
field.description: Quoted level for the Dealer. Can be expressed as basis points spread, percentage yield, or percentage of par price, as specified in DealerQuotedPriceType

field.name: DealerQuoteOrdQty
field.description: Quoted size for the Dealer. Always expressed in par

field.name: DealerQuoteText
field.description: Free text comment field

field.name: CompetitiveStatus
field.description: Indicates the competitive status of each dealer quote (Done, Covered, Missed etc).

field.name: DealerQuoteFxRate
field.description: Quoted FX rate for each Dealer. Float. Direction is determined by SettlCurrFxRateCalc (tag 156)

field.name: DirtyPrice
field.description: All-in USD dirty price for the local market trades with FX component.

field.name: OppBroker
field.description:
same as official tag 337 or 9100
** ADDED TO FIX 4.2 AS TAG: 375 (ContraBroker) **

field.name: OmnibusAccount
field.description:
Indicates the types of customer or account requesting the order. Values are 1 For own account
2 For clearing members house account
3 For the account of another member present
4 For any other customer account

field.name: CtiCode
field.description:
Indicates the types of customer or account requesting the order. Values are 1 For own account
2 For clearing members house account
3 For the account of another member present
4 For any other customer account

field.name: SessionIndicator
field.description: Indicates the routing to an executing system G Globex trading engine

field.name: PrevExpERCReferenceNumber
field.description: Valid on FIX MsgType 8. FIX 4.2 Format: String. 10-byte Expanded Activity ID on an ERC. This tag is a concatenation of a 5-digit Reference number, followed by a 5-digit Sequence number.Both reference number and sequence number will start at 00001 (i.e. 0000100001). The PrevExpERCReferenceNumber is the activity ID associated with the previous Execution Report or ERC for the same order.

field.name: ProductComplex
field.description: High level product type. N for Energy A for Aggs E for Equity ... (more granularity than CFICode)

field.name: FeeBilling
field.description:
Type of clearing fee. Values are B CBOE member trading
C Non-member rate (customer)
E Equity member rate
H 106H/J Firms
L Lessee/106.F employees

field.name: GiveUpFirm
field.description: Identifies the clearing member firm to which the fill was given up.

field.name: CmtaGiveupCD
field.description:
Indicates if the order is a give-up or CMTA trade. Values are T CMTA
G Give-up

field.name: BackOfficeText
field.description: Back office information. TOPS Route sends this information to the back office system

field.name: PostExecutionAllocation
field.description: "PEA" = only valid value

field.name: OppHouse
field.description: Indicates the house of the contraBroker

field.name: AllocReceiverIdtype
field.description: 1=email,2=uuid

field.name: TimeIn
field.description: Time order is received by exchange

field.name: BrokerReceiptTime
field.description: Time that the broker receives the order

field.name: TimeBracketCode
field.description: Indicates the time bracket of an order fill.

field.name: LOGIN_ROUTE_ID
field.description: This tag shall contain the id used for login and routing purposes

field.name: CorrelationClOrdID
field.description: Id common to new order and subsequent series of requests against that order. Used for reporting.

field.name: TrdRegTimestampTimeIn
field.description: Timestamp source for Time In timestamp. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: TrdRegTimestampOriginBrkReceipt
field.description: Timestamp source for Broker Receipt timestamp. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: TrdRegTimestampOriginExecution
field.description: Timestamp soource for Exectution timestamp. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: TimeOut
field.description: Timestamp of fill being reported from the pit to the trading floor booth. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: TrdRegTimestampOriginTimeOut
field.description: Timestamp source of Time Out timestamp. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: DiscretionPx
field.description: The Discretion Price of the order. This price is the limit for the DiscretionQty can be traded at. The value is an absolute price.

field.name: FillUserID
field.description: Clerk or trader entering the fill into the fill reporting system. (Potentially a Party Role.)

field.name: FillTerminalID
field.description: ID of station reporting fill. (Similar to FIX 4.3 Party Role of Executing System.)

field.name: FillSeqNum
field.description: Sequence number assigned to the fill by the station reporting it.

field.name: FillNumLines
field.description: Total number of fills being reported by station under a single FillSeqNum.

field.name: FillLineNum
field.description: Reference to a specific fill being reported under a single FillSeqNum. (See custom field FillNumLines.)

field.name: OrderLegNum
field.description: When reporting fill, references the leg number in the order.

field.name: TradeLiquidityIndicator
field.description: Indicates whether a trade adds liquidity (A) or removes liquidity (R) from the marketplace.

field.name: TLTCFlag
field.description: Fill being reported is flagged Too Late To Cancel when a cancel/replace or cancel request was received after the execution.

field.name: FormattedLastPx
field.description: LastPx formatted for processing by post-trade systems.

field.name: PrintedTicketLabel
field.description: Label printed on trading floor order ticket.

field.name: PartyRoleExecutingTrader
field.description: Trader executing the order. (Exists in FIX 4.3 as repeating group.)

field.name: PartyRoleClearingFirm
field.description: Clearing firm of executed order. (Exists in FIX 4.3 as repeating group.)

field.name: PartyRoleClearingOrg
field.description: Clearing organization for executed order. (Exists in FIX 4.4 as repeating group.)

field.name: ClearingSecurityID
field.description: Security ID as assigned by clearing organization. (Combination of FIX 4.4 SecurityIDSource and SecurityID.)

field.name: ClearingStrikePx
field.description: Strike price as formatted by clearing organization.

field.name: MIFIDBestExecutionReqd
field.description:
Indicates whether the broker is to execute the order using the Best Execution Policy defined with the customer (MIFID directive)
Valid values : Y = Indicates the broker should execute the order using the Best Execution Policy N = Indicates the broker should NOT execute the order using the Best Execution Policy
(optional)

field.name: PIPSequentialNo
field.description: Assigned by an exchange to identify a particular price improvement phase for a particular instrument

field.name: PIPExpiryTime
field.description: Indicates the time when an instrument price improvement phase will expire

field.name: PIPExpiryDuration
field.description: Indicates the duration in seconds of an instrument price improvement phase

field.name: PIPManagementType
field.description:
Indicates the type of management requested for an order than will initiate a price improvement phase for an instrument. Possible values are:
0 = The clients price improvement is managed manually 1 = The clients price improvement is managed by the exchange

field.name: PIPImprovementType
field.description: Indicates how the exchange should manage a client's price improvement order. Possible values are: 0 = The client's price improvement will be managed manually 1 = Management by joining the better price 2 = Management by increasing by + one Improvement tick the better price

field.name: PIPMaxPrice
field.description: Indicates the price to not exceed for a price improvement order that is managed by the exchange

field.name: OmgeoSwiftOldValue
field.description: null

field.name: OmgeoSwiftNewValue
field.description: null

field.name: MaxOrderQty
field.description: Indicates the maximum order quantity allowed for a particular instrument

field.name: MinOrderQty
field.description: Indicates the minimum order quantity allowed for a particular instrument

field.name: ChgFromSettlmnt
field.description: Indicates the change in an instrument price from the previous day's settlement price

field.name: ChgFromSettlmntDirection
field.description: Indicates the direction of change of an instrument price from the instrument's previous day settlement price '+' = increase '-' = decrease ' ' = no change

field.name: StrikePriceCode
field.description: Standard Code For Expressing Option Strike Price

field.name: StrikePriceCurrency
field.description: Specifies the currency of the strike price. USD = US$, CAN = Canadian $

field.name: InstrumentExternalCode
field.description: The external code for an instrument. Sometimes referred to as the instrument contract name. Consists of the instrument symbol, expiration month code, and expiration year. For options, a put/call indication and strike price are also included. An example code at BOX for an IBM Put option with a July 2003 expiration and $80 strike price would be IBMS03P80.00. The conventions may be different for other exchanges.

field.name: OptionSponsorType
field.description: Indicates Option Sponsor Type 0 = Regular 1 = Societe Generale

field.name: RemainingFills
field.description:
Indicates if any more fills will be occurring. Takes the same value as a partial fill indicator for all cases except FAK orders. In the case of FAK orders, this field indicates that no more fills will be occurring even if the order is not completely filled and explains why the leaves quantity is set to 0.
Possible Values 0 = No more fills 1 = More fills

field.name: OrigOrdQty
field.description: The original quantity of an order

field.name: ExpositionOrderType
field.description: Indicates the type of an order that is being exposed 1=Normal 2=No NBBO Check 3=No IML 4=Outbound 5=P Inbound 6=PA Inbound

field.name: OrderExpositionEndTime
field.description: The end time for an order exposition

field.name: ClearingLastPx
field.description: LastPx as formatted by clearing organization.

field.name: OmgeoFXDealCurrencyCode
field.description: Allows the user to instruct the recipient of a settlement instruction to perform an FX deal.

field.name: ClearingOrdType
field.description: Order types as defined by clearing organization.

field.name: ClearingBusCycle
field.description: Business cycle as defined by clearing organization.

field.name: AddInstText
field.description: Additional text-based instructions for order execution.

field.name: TFPossRetransFlag
field.description: Flags message as possible retransmission for printing on trading floor order ticket.

field.name: TFConfirmRequest
field.description: Indicates confirmation of cancel is requested from the trading floor.

field.name: TLTCClOrdRefID
field.description: Refers to ClOrdID on fill being reported Too Late To Cancel. See custom tag 9731 TLTCFlag.

field.name: OFMOverride
field.description: Flag indicating the order quantity stipulated on Replace Request should be entered into the market as stated - without reduction for any fills that have occurred.

field.name: SecondaryExecID
field.description: For FIX 4.2 (contains the trade number in the fill notice - execution report). Added in FIX 4.3 as tag 527 - SecondaryExecID.

field.name: ExchangeQuoteReqID
field.description: Quote Request ID generated by the Exchange returned to the clients in the quote acknowledgment message (tag 35 = b) in response to their Quote Request message.

field.name: MMAccount
field.description: Account number information used in Quote related messages in FIX 4.2

field.name: NoProcessedEntries
field.description: Number of quotes successfully accepted (if in response to a Mass Quote message) or number of quotes successfully cancelled (if in response to a Quote Cancel message).

field.name: MMProtectionReset
field.description: When MM Protection is triggered, the Trading Engine will not accept any new Quotes from the Market Maker for that Product Group until it receives a Mass Quote Message with the MMProtectionReset flag set to 1.

field.name: CancelledSymbol
field.description: Symbol cancelled for an unsollicited Quote Ack message.

field.name: UnsolicitedCancelType
field.description: Type of the cancel generated by engine. A: Cancel all quotes on disconnect B: Cancel all quotes on logout C: Cancel all by Operations D: Cancel Instrument Group by Operations E: Quote Expired F: Cancelled by Market Maker Protection G: Cancel Instrument Group when too many incorrect quotes submitted.

field.name: AutoQuoteRequest
field.description: Boolean flag (Y/N) to automatically send a Quote Request message following the Security Definition (35=d) message. This might be used when users create an instrument using the Security Definition Request (35=c) message.

field.name: Billable
field.description: Indicates whether an order incur specialist fee. Y=Yes, N=No.

field.name: CMSLine1A
field.description: CMS Line1A. Used for specifying routing instructions, such as NYSE Direct+(NY NX), booth routing(NY OVR B-xx), Amex or NYSE override (NY OVR), crossing session (NY OS), etc.

field.name: UserDefinedInstrument
field.description: Boolean field to tell if the instrument defined by the Security Definition message is a user defined instrument or not.

field.name: CrossOrdBidQty
field.description: Quantity of the buy side of cross requests

field.name: CrossOrdAskQty
field.description: Quantity of the ask side of cross requests

field.name: LastCrossReqTime
field.description: Timestamp of the last cross request received for an instrument

field.name: QuoteReqBidQty
field.description: Indicates the quantity of the bid side of quote requests in an instrument's market

field.name: QuoteReqAskQty
field.description: Indicates the quantity of the ask side of quote requests in an instrument's market

field.name: LastQuoteReqTime
field.description: Time of the last quote request received for an instrument

field.name: BangStyle
field.description: Tag 9786 allows clients to specify the style of bang applied to each order on an individual basis.S=Single and N=Normal

field.name: DisplayFactor
field.description: Multiplier to convert electronic prices sent over fix to display prices.

field.name: SpreadExecID
field.description: Equivalent to the ExecID of a spread when dealing with multi-leg securities.

field.name: SpreadSecurityID
field.description: SecurityID for the spread related to the leg reported as SecurityID in the message Execution Report.

field.name: ResponseRequested
field.description: Used to indicate if a response is requested (or required) from the e-mail recipient

field.name: OriginalEmailThreadID
field.description: Original Email Thread ID to which this e-mail message is in reply

field.name: DbExecID
field.description: Execution Id assigned to both sides of a transaction and passed back to each party in the execution report.

field.name: AttributedQuote
field.description: Tag assigned to an order to indicate that the submitter wants to be identified on the Archipelago quote feed. The submitter would be identified with their Archipelago ETPID.

field.name: Proactive if Locked
field.description: When set it will designate an order sent as a PNP to go proactive if it locks the market.

field.name: Prospectus Indicator
field.description: Indicates that an order should be considered part of a prospectus offering

field.name: Don't Arb
field.description: If a block trade occurs at an away market an order container the don't arb flag will re-price to the execution price of the block trade.

field.name: ARCAEx News Type
field.description: enumerated value indicating the type of ARCAEx news message

field.name: AllocReceiverId
field.description: Can be internet e-mail or Bloomberg UUID

field.name: VWAPType
field.description: Indicates type of VWAP execution client wishes Bloomberg Tradebook to deliver. Used for non-US securities only. Valid values: V1=session 1 V2=session 2 V3=full day V4=point of trade

field.name: PriceDisplayFormat
field.description: Format to use to display the price on the screen.

field.name: SecuritySubType
field.description:
Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType. Same as 762 in FIX 4.4.
For SecurityType="MLEG" markets can provide the name of the option or futures strategy, such as Calendar, Vertical, Butterfly, etc. NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties

field.name: BloombergServerID
field.description: Identifier of the Bloomberg server that generated an order and allocation. Used for internal routing purposes. String - upto16 characters

field.name: TradingSystemID
field.description: Identifier of the Trading System that processed an order or allocation. Used for internal routing purposes. String - upto 16 characters

field.name: ZSpread
field.description: <Spread or Benchmark Curve Data> Contains the Zero Coupon spread which is the difference between the Corp Yield and the zero-coupon Yield. Format -NNN.DDD

field.name: ISpread
field.description: Contains the Interest Rate Swap spread which is the difference between the Corp Yield and the IRS Yield. Format -NNN.DDD

field.name: ASWSpread
field.description: Contains Asset Swap spread which is the difference between the Corp Yield and the ASW Yield. Format -NNN.DDD

field.name: RegFeeFlag
field.description: Reserved for future use by Nasdaq.

field.name: OmgeoCommissionSharingType
field.description: Used inside the BrokerOfCredit/Directed Commission Nested Party to indicate type of commission sharing. Allowed values are: CLDI (client directed); SOFT (soft dollar); STEP (step out trade); STPI (step in trade).

field.name: OmgeoTPAssignedTime
field.description: Date and time when the Omgeo Third Party generated the message.

field.name: VWAPOrder
field.description: This tag initiates a VWAP strategy for the order.Valid values:9810=0(off),1(on)

field.name: VWAPStart
field.description: VWAP start time (GMT)

field.name: VWAPStop
field.description: VWAP stop time (GMT)

field.name: VWAPMatching
field.description: This tag specifies if the VWAP order will be eligible for matching (U.S orders only) 9813=0(not eligible) 9813=1(eligible)

field.name: VWAPExceed
field.description: This tag specifies that the counterparty initiating the order acknowledges and accepts that the total order quantity exceeds a certain percentage of the typical daily volume.Absence of this tag or a 0 value will result in a reject if 38>%TDV 9814=0 9814=1 (acknowledgement)

field.name: FireQuantity
field.description: The quantity of an IOC order, in shares, that system sends to exchange (with discretion) when other parameters are met.Order will be rejected if the quantity is an invalid board lot.

field.name: TickMultiplier
field.description: Whole numbers only. Multiply this value with appropriate Tick increment (based on current security price and GTEX Tick Rules) to calculate the Discretion Quantity.

field.name: MinorCtrlNbr
field.description: NASDAQ-assigned 10-char control number used to identify each one of the minor trades used for a M2 trade match with the major trade.

field.name: Blockbuster Sizable Action Code
field.description: A = Allow I = Inhibit For trade reporting.

field.name: Inhibit Trade Indicator
field.description: Valid values: B = Buy side clearing firm inhibited the trade S = Sell side clearing firm inhibited the trade blank = Neither clearing firm has inhibited the trade A = One or both clearing firms have allowed the trade, as required.

field.name: Blockbuster Sizable Start Time
field.description: Entry time of the blockbuster or sizable trade.

field.name: Blockbuster Sizable Action Time
field.description: Time of receipt of action input or expiration of review period.

field.name: ClearingPrice
field.description: Price inclusive of commissions.

field.name: NetTradeLimitInd
field.description: Contains "M" when the dollar amount of this trade contributes to the MM's Net Amount Traded (NAT) so as to exceed the MM's Net Trade Limit (NTL), or "O" when the dollar amount of this trade contributes to the OE's NAT so as to exceed the OE's NTL.

field.name: ClearingBroker
field.description: Clearing broker ID.

field.name: ReportingGUID
field.description: MPID of give up on the trade reporting party side.

field.name: NonReportingGUID
field.description: MPID of give up on the non-trade reporting party side.

field.name: DeskTraderID
field.description: Contains desk/trader ID.

field.name: RelativeGTTLife
field.description: Life of GTT order rather than an expire time.

field.name: ComplaintCode
field.description: 91 = block trade through 92 = locked market 93 = lock/ship 94 = pre open report 95 = quote error 96 = quote change 97 = resend comm. 98 = trade through 99 = why cancel

field.name: IntroBrokerInd
field.description: The Introducing Broker is the firm who gives-up another firm during the execution of the trade. Valid values: A = Active S = Suspended

field.name: ExecBrokerInd
field.description: The Executing Brokers are those firms on either side who "own" the trade. Valid values: A = Active S = Suspended

field.name: ClearBrokerInd
field.description: The Clearing Brokers are those firms who will clear the trade. Valid values: A = Active S = Suspended

field.name: ResponsibilityInd
field.description: The firm which takes responsibility for trade reporting functions. Valid values: Y = Yes N = No

field.name: TradeRepAvailInd
field.description: States denoting the extent of a firm's participation in Trade Reporting. Valid values: N = Not ready A = Available E = Effective Tomorrow U = Unavailable for technical reasons

field.name: MajorClearingInd
field.description: Signifies that the CBID in the message is the MMID's major clearing firm. A self-clearing firm will always be denoted as major. Valid values: M = Major N = not a major arrangement

field.name: RiskMgmtInd
field.description: Designates that the clearing relationship in this message is functionally Active. It also assigns responsibility to the correspondent or the clearing firm for the entry of all T+2 to T+N entries. Valid values for self-clearing firms are A, M, and D. Valid values: A = Active & correspondent cannot enter As of T+2 to T+N trades (except self-clearing) M = Active with Super-Cap Marker & correspondent cannot enter As of T+2 to T+N trades (except self-clearing) Y = Active & correspondent can enter As of T+2 to T+N trades (except self-clearing) N = Active with Super-Cap Marker, correspondent (non-self clearing) can enter As-of T+2 to T+N trades D = Deleted

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyRole
field.description: Type of third party being identified

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyType
field.description: This field identifies the type of format used to identify the party

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyValue
field.description: Identity of the party specified as a character string

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyName
field.description: The actual name of the organization

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyStatus
field.description: The status of communication with the third party

field.name: OmgeoThirdPartyStatusTime
field.description: The time the third party status was assigned to the allocation by Central Trade Manager (CTM)

field.name: OmgeoTPAssignedID
field.description: The identifier assigned to the allocation by the third party upon receipt

field.name: OmgeoTPReason
field.description: A free form text field for communication of additional information from the third party to Central Trade Manager (CTM)

field.name: OmgeoNoThirdPartyData
field.description: This field indicates the number of Third Party Data blocks that are provided on the message.

field.name: NewCtrlNbr
field.description: NASDAQ-assigned control number that will be used to identify the new split trade created from the M2 trade match that resulted from splitting either the major trade or one of the minor trades. If there was no new trade created, this field will contain 0 (zero).

field.name: LockedInStatus
field.description: Contains the current status of the locked in trade.
